column1: There are two types of people in this world

You are staying at a hotel for a night. You have just arrived, are upstairs, in your room, unpacking. Everyone else in the hotel seems nice and friendly, except for one- the person next door. You rarely see him enter or exit the room, he's always a mess, and every question you ask him always leads to dry, one word responses. Generally speaking, he just seems to give off an unsettling vibe. Fortunately, the hotel you're staying in has a swimming pool, and you go there later that day. When you are there, you see someone sitting on a chair at the edge of the pool, and you recognize him instantly- the person next door. He definitely isn't there to swim, because he's wearing a hoodie and jeans, and he's just sitting there, watching your every move. Five minutes later, he was still there, so you leave. Five minutes after you arrive back to your room, you hear a knock at the door, followed by a voice yelling, "Housekeeping!". But you don't answer the door, because you recognize the low, raspy smoker's voice- it's the person next door. You look through the peephole, and see that he doesn't have any towels. At this point, you know for sure he wants to come in for a very sinister reason. What do you do?
